originalText.text: I would not recommend this store. The prices are overpriced and they also charge extra when checking out items, than the amount the items are listed for. Also they don't enforce the rule of taking everyone's bag at the door, so they pick and choose who's bag they will take. The last straw for me with this store was when I went to the store and they took my 8 years old sons book bag. And I was completely fine with this because it's the rule. However when I fully stepped into the store I was surprised to see a grown woman with a large book bag on her back, and two other children with book bags on their backs, in the store. When I mentioned it to the guy that works there he wouldn't acknowledge my point, and kept asking me am I done shopping, and when I'm done I will get my son's books bag back. I got a sense that he was irritated with me mentioning this. I just thought it was weird and unprofessional to not enforce the rule for everyone. So I left without purchasing anything from there. I already started shopping online mostly to save money because of their prices but after this I realized I need to just completely avoid this store cuz there are better alternatives out there. So for household products I will go locally to dollar tree or CVS and for groceries I shop online on Amazon fresh and that has been a better experience for me. And unfortunately despite the negative reviews and the complaints I'm sure this store has received, it will continue to thrive in this community.
